## Memory Injection Protocol

**BEFORE executing any command**, search L9 memory via MCP server:

```bash
# 1. Preferences and patterns for this command type (via MCP search_memory tool)
python3 agents/cursor/cursor_memory_client.py search "preferences [command_name]"

# 2. Lessons and errors relevant to task (via MCP search_memory tool)
python3 agents/cursor/cursor_memory_client.py search "lessons errors [task_keywords]"

# 3. Context-specific knowledge (via MCP search_memory tool)
python3 agents/cursor/cursor_memory_client.py search "[domain] [component] patterns"
```

**Note:** All searches use MCP server (PRIMARY). Client falls back to HTTP only if MCP unreachable.

### Injection Output Format

```
## 🧠 MEMORY CONTEXT INJECTED

### Preferences
- [preference 1]
- [preference 2]

### Relevant Lessons
- [lesson 1]
- [lesson 2]

### Context
- [context item]

📍 Proceeding with command execution...
```

